node.title: The Internet Broke Brand Loyalty
node.description: You loved TikTok leggings. Will you ever buy them again?

node.title: White Castle Joins OnlyFans to Share Spicy Thanksgiving Stuffing Recipes
node.description: The recipes for the Bacon Jalapeño Cheese Slider Stuffing and Southwest Jalapeño Cheese Slider Stuffing were shared on OnlyFans.

node.title: Paul Gosar, Censured Over Anime Meme, Says 7 Siblings Are 'Horrific to Me'
node.description: The Republican was censured by the House for sharing a clip that showed him killing Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez. He has also been denounced by his brothers and sisters.

node.title: Jeremy Renner Takes Aim at TV in ‘Hawkeye’ and ‘Mayor of Kingstown’
node.description: The “Avengers” star has two new streaming series: one based on his Marvel superhero character and another that recalls his gritty roles in “The Hurt Locker” and “The Town.”

node.title: The Little Lad? Berries and Cream? Call It Performance Art.
node.description: Jack Ferver, the creator of a well-regarded body of dance-theater works, has also become a TikTok phenomenon because of a Starburst ad from 2007.

node.title: Bloodied Venezuelan Opposition Returns to Elections for First Time in Years
node.description: With little hope of a fair vote, opposition candidates take a desperate risk to gain any edge against Venezuela’s entrenched autocrat, Nicolás Maduro.

node.title: Kamala Harris Will Be First Woman to Hold Presidential Powers as Biden Undergoes Physical
node.description: President Joe Biden will be placed under anesthesia Friday for a routine colonoscopy.

node.title: Woman Left Shaking With 'Anger and Disgust' After Her Rapist Avoids Jail
node.description: "It was as if I was being victimized all over again," the woman said after a judge handed Christopher Belter a sentence of eight years of probation.

node.title: CDC: Vials labeled "Smallpox" found in lab have no trace of virus
node.description: The CDC had said that the vials "were incidentally discovered by a laboratory worker" who cleaning out the freezer.

node.title: House Passes the Largest Expenditure on Climate in U.S. History
node.description: The $555 billion package is designed to lure the country away from fossil fuels. It faces an uncertain path in the Senate.

node.title: House Narrowly Passes Biden’s Social Safety Net and Climate Bill
node.description: The vote was months in the making for the roughly $2 trillion measure, one of the most consequential bills in decades. Now it faces a difficult path in the Senate.

node.title: China’s Influence Looms Over Blinken’s Africa Visit
node.description: On a stop in Nigeria, the secretary of state said the U.S. would no longer treat African countries as pawns in a global game. But American competition with Beijing was hard to overlook.

node.title: Watch Live: Biden pardons turkeys Peanut Butter and Jelly ahead of Thanksgiving
node.description: The turkeys weigh about 40 pounds each and were raised in Jasper, Indiana.

node.title: AstroWorld Lawsuits Could Result in Billions of Dollars of Settlements
node.description: Ten people have now died as a result of the deadly crush that took place at the Houston festival earlier this month.

node.title: GOP governors confident they'll dominate Democrats in 2022
node.description: RGA Chair Doug Ducey said Kansas, Maine, Michigan, New Mexico, Pennsylvania and Wisconsin will be among the top targets for the GOP to flip next year.

node.title: Stunning Partial Lunar Eclipse Photos Show Moon Appearing Red Around the World
node.description: The event was the longest partial lunar eclipse since 1440, clocking in at around three-and-a-half hours.

node.title: Majority Think Joe Biden's Age Interfering With His Ability to Be President: Poll
node.description: The president is the oldest person to serve as commander in chief in the history of the United States.

node.title: Entire House GOP Opposes Biden's $1.7T Bill but 42 Percent of Republicans Voters Back It
node.description: Substantial majorities of Republican voters also back some of the legislation's key provisions, according to new polling.

node.title: Childhood photo helped a woman uncover a killer in her family tree
node.description: All Chelsea Rustad had been trying to do was learn the name of her great grandparents. What she uncovered was a secret that was buried much deeper.

node.title: Puff Bar CEOs on the "mystery" behind the popular e-cigarette brand
node.description: The market for Puff Bar exploded in early 2020 after the FDA banned candy and fruit-flavored e-cigarettes, like Juul, citing their popularity among teens.

node.title: Justice Department seeks 4-year term for wife of "El Chapo"
node.description: Emma Coronel Aispuro pleaded guilty to counts including drug trafficking and money laundering. Prosecutors said she was a go-between for the Mexican drug kingpin with his associates.

node.title: Funeral home sued for $88M after alleged body mix-up
node.description: Eleven siblings say the home put the wrong body in their mother's plot evne though the funeral director was warned about what was happening. They're claiming gross negligence.

node.title: This Holographic Camera Can See Around Corners, Under Human Skin
node.description: The technology developed at Northwestern University uses walls and other obscuring surfaces to scatter light like a mirror and build an image of hidden objects.

node.title: Taiwan Could Be First Domino in Chinese Land Grab Across Asia
node.description: Experts discuss with Newsweek what would happen next if China invades Taiwan.

node.title: No verdict yet in Rittenhouse trial after over 20 hours of deliberations
node.description: Defense attorney Mark Richards said this is the longest deliberation he has ever had in his career as a defense trial attorney.

node.title: F.D.A. Authorizes Coronavirus Booster Shots for All Adults
node.description: If the C.D.C. agrees, adults who received a second shot of the Pfizer or Moderna vaccine at least six months ago could be eligible by this weekend.

node.title: What's behind the push for a fourth stimulus check
node.description: IRS has distributed almost 170 million payments. But hardship remains widespread as the Delta variant spreads.

node.title: FDA authorizes COVID vaccine boosters for all adults
node.description: If the CDC echoes the FDA's decision, it could clear the way for third doses for all adults by the weekend.

node.title: These Influencers Found the Zillow Houses We Love to Hate
node.description: Online listing sites offer a window into what is possible, but the social media accounts that lampoon them give us the chance to ogle what never should have been.

node.title: One meme stock lawsuit against Robinhood is dismissed, but others loom.
node.description: The suit was part of a proposed three-part class action suit against Robinhood and others over their roles in January’s GameStop trading frenzy.

node.title: Does the Songwriter of ‘I Love L.A.’ Actually Love L.A.?
node.description: The city’s anthem is unmistakably tongue-in-cheek.

node.title: Britain outlaws Palestinian militant group Hamas
node.description: Announcing the decision, Britain's Interior Minister says "Hamas has significant terrorist capability, including access to extensive and sophisticated weaponry", while the militant group says the move shows "absolute bias toward the Israeli occupation".

node.title: MSNBC banned from Kyle Rittenhouse trial after bus incident
node.description: NBC News said a freelancer was cited for a traffic violation near the jury vehicle and he "never contacted or intended to contact the jurors during deliberations, and never photographed or intended to photograph them."

node.title: A victim warns that her rapist "will offend again" after he avoids jail time
node.description: Christopher Belter pleaded guilty to sex crimes against four teenage girls. He was sentenced to eight years of probation.

node.title: Biden heading to Walter Reed for annual physical on eve of his birthday
node.description: The president's last annual physical was in 2019.
